  "title": "Marketing Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>📌 Job Overview</p><p>A <strong>Marketing Coordinator</strong> helps plan, implement, and monitor marketing campaigns to promote a company’s products or services. They collaborate with internal teams and external vendors to ensure campaigns run smoothly and align with business goals.</p><p>🎯 Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li><strong>Campaign Support:</strong> Assist in planning, implementing, and tracking marketing campaigns across digital and offline channels.</li><li><strong>Market Research:</strong> Conduct research on competitors, consumer trends, and industry developments to inform strategy.</li><li><strong>Content Creation:</strong> Develop marketing materials such as social media posts, blog articles, brochures, and email newsletters.</li><li><strong>Event Coordination:</strong> Organize trade shows, conferences, and promotional events, ensuring logistics and branding are handled.</li><li><strong>Performance Tracking:</strong> Monitor campaign metrics using analytics tools and prepare reports on effectiveness.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Work with designers, writers, and external vendors to produce marketing assets.</li><li><strong>Brand Management:</strong> Ensure all marketing materials align with the company’s brand identity and messaging.</li></ul><p>🛠️ Skills & Qualifications</p><ul><li>Strong communication and organizational skills.</li><li>Ability to multitask and manage deadlines.</li><li>Creative thinking with attention to detail.</li><li>no experience needed</li></ul><p>💡 Why This Role Matters</p><p>Marketing Coordinators are the <strong>engine room of the marketing team</strong>. They ensure that strategies are executed effectively, campaigns are tracked, and brand presence remains strong. Without them, marketing plans often fail to translate into action.</p>",
